# SDLC Core Rule

Before any implementation task:

1. Read `.github/sdlc-config.json`.
2. Read `.github/copilot-instructions.md`.
3. Apply relevant rules from `.cursor/rules/` based on file type and task intent.

Canonical mapping:

- `.github/agents/*.agent.md` -> `.cursor/agents/*.agent.md`
- `.github/skills/*/SKILL.md` -> `.cursor/skills/*.md`
- `.github/instructions/*.instructions.md` -> `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`

Execution constraints:

- Keep `.github` files authoritative.
- Update `.cursor` compatibility files when `.github` SDLC files change.
- Preserve project structure and conventions from `.github/sdlc-config.json`.
